One of the rules I use to decide how good a marginal hand is what I call "Quick Trick" points. To use it I count my Quick Tricks. In this case North has 4 Quick Tricks.|
PG| ***** 19 ***** |


NT|^B@2
There are a possible 8 quick tricks (2 in each suit). Since there are 40 HCP, each quick trick is worth around 5 points (40 / 8).|
PG| ***** 20 ***** |


NT|^B@2
